TP (True Positive): correctly predicted positive
TN (True Negative): correctly predicted negative
FP (False Positive): incorrectly predicted positive
FN (False Negative): incorrectly predicted negative
🔹 Accuracy
Measures overall correctness.

Accuracy=TP+TN+FP+FNTP+TN
🔹 Precision
Out of predicted positives, how many were actually correct.

Precision=TP+FPTP
🔹 Recall (Sensitivity)
Out of actual positives, how many were correctly identified.

Recall=TP+FNTP
🔹 F1 Score
Harmonic mean of Precision and Recall.

F1 Score=2×Precision+RecallPrecision×Recall
🔹 Alternative F1 Formula (direct)
You can also compute it directly from TP, FP, FN:

F1 Score=2TP+FP+FN2TP
